populations safe from pandemics =E2=80=93 a new challenge to sit above =
equality.

=20

So articles like this need to targeted specifically at corporate leaders =
because they are the ones that are in a position to enact policy and =
change. And I don=E2=80=99t understand why a corporate leader would be =
focussed on Prioritize, Protect and Plan =E2=80=93 it=E2=80=99s the =
wrong lens?

=20

More like:

*	I need a vibrant company that is either good to its shareholders or =
good to whichever stakeholders I am targeting
*	Therefore I need a vibrant stable environment=20
*	And I need to be able to access the talent I need

=20

So yes I need to support the well being of workers because I need =
workers and consumer.

=20

And corporate leaders don=E2=80=99t care about vulnerable people unless =
they are my consumers =E2=80=93 I think in the future we will learn to =
focus less on the vulnerable because of the impact on the whole =
=E2=80=93 and as long as the environment remains vibrant and stable no =
leader will care

=20

Plan for a better future? All we can do is try and persuade corporate =
leaders that they have an interest in supporting an equitable society =
=E2=80=93 but we need to be realistic about how far this interest will =
go.

=20

I=E2=80=99ve been reading various right wing news outlets to keep myself =
balanced =E2=80=93 and this makes me frustrated with some fluffy =
articles like this =E2=80=93 there is no support for it in the wider =
world =E2=80=93 in my humble opinion!

